  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Strengthening of Life-Saving Response through Provision of Emergency Water, Sanitation and Hygiene (WASH) Assistance and Mobility Tracking of Affected Communities.</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In coordination and collaboration with relevant government disaster response mechanisms, through this project, IOM is supporting emergency provision of safe water and sanitation services in the Elgon Region, (Bududa and Sironko Districts) and South Western (Bundibugyo District) in Uganda, to respond to the heavy rains in the country. In addition, the project is supporting the overall flood response operations by providing vital information regarding the flood affected communities through its Displacement Tracking Matrix (DTM) activities in the Elgon Region, (Bududa and Sironko Districts) and South Western (Bundibugyo District).</narrative>
  </description>
